<taxonomicName id="CC95EF1445DE39715E9F8C435D3960CF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosum">Chenopodium foliosum</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1A854F82D1911F3BE1615A2298D1C8C4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="50" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatum">C. capitatum</taxonomicName>
(2) in having more dentate leaves and bracts, bracteate upper glomerules which are red (not reddish violet) in colour, and larger seeds with flat to grooved edge. - See also 
<taxonomicName id="808AD283B149707693D3D0BD8EAFFDCC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exsuccum">C. exsuccum</taxonomicName>
(rare casual).
</paragraph>
